storyInfo: The Rhodes Island Field Personnel are attacked by a strange mutated creature, when suddenly they receive a distress signal from a hidden Rhodes Island Safe House. The members of the squad decide to investigate.

attributes.content: Last one here!
attributes.name: Schwarz

attributes.content: Everyone else!? Any wounded?
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: No worries here.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: None here, either.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Communications equipment?
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: Unharmed.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Is this its burrow? ...Strange.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: They seemed like sand beasts, at least?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Sand beasts, of this size? Over two meters long?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: ...I've spent the better part of my life in these wastelands, but never have I seen a sand beast capable of digging holes.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: ...These creatures have Originium crystals on their bodies.
attributes.name: Schwarz

attributes.content: Possibly biological mutations caused by Originium pollution, then?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: There's no nomadic cities, no factories and no mines. How does Originium pollution even happen here?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Could it have been a Catastrophe's fault?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: You'd be underestimating nature. Wildlife knows Catastrophes far better than we do. These creatures would've been the first to avoid Originium pollution.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Cities can be torn apart by Catastrophes while the wildlife emerges untouched
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: —Nature in this world is ruthless when it wants to eliminate you. If you don't have some way of dealing with Originium, your time as a living species won't be long.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I think... I have a hypothesis. Like ordinary Originium Slugs, the body's outer shell could have absorbed Originium into its makeup, while its innards remain clean and uncorrupted.
attributes.name: Schwarz

attributes.content: On that note, has P.R.T.S ever recorded any similar cases?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: None. Not even for the Ironforge City leakage incident in Columbia, and that's the first thing you'd think of.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Sand beasts are docile creatures by nature. Originium shouldn't change them so drastically, and I can't imagine anything short of Arts would make them outright aggressive.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: Stay vigilant. Don't let your guard down.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: ...Arts? A Caster? I just hope this doesn't complicate things for us.
attributes.name: Schwarz

attributes.content: Don't let it worry you too much. We'll continue on as we were, anyhow.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: Understood.
attributes.name: Schwarz

attributes.content: Is this... a Rhodes Island emergency rescue signal?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Is it another Rhodes Island field team, maybe?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: ...oh, thank hea......meone finally answered!
...pl......help us......equesting support...
This is a Rhodes Island Field Personnel Team. If you receive this, please reply.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: This is......Long Spring......Watchtower 33...
...mob......currently...
...they've come in!
Calm down! Operator, tell us what's happened!
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: The signal's very poor. They're coming through intermittent.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: ...help us......plea......ing you—

attributes.text: An burst of sharp static, and communications break off.

attributes.content: Well, that's not good.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: What does Watchtower 33 refer to?
attributes.name: Schwarz

attributes.content: From the sound of it, it seemed like a Rhodes Island safehouse's code name.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: A safehouse? The mission brief didn't mention any safehouses around here.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Truthfully, in a few areas, Rhodes Island will make a habit of hiding some safehouses, out of the way. For use in very particular field missions.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: But we ourselves don't know where Watchtower 33 is.
attributes.name: Schwarz

attributes.content: Long Spring... Long Spring...
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: That name rings a faint bell. If you could let me see the map for a second.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: Hmm...
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: Here, if I'm not mistaken. Following about twenty kilometers north from Trumhill, you should find another canyon. That canyon had a little village near it, I'm sure of it.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: That village, years ago, had a well. One of the very few reliable water sources for miles around.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: So that's why it's Long Spring?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: So. What do we do next? Change of plans?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Or we can try and make for Phecon overnight, get in touch with the branch office and see what assistance we can procure from them.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: ...I worry the operator in the safehouse may not last long enough for that.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: All of you, keep going until you reach Phecon, and find some support or other there if you can.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: I'll head for Long Spring and see what the situation is. Don't you worry, I know this land very, very well. Indeed, I can afford to be more flexible on my lonesome.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: If things get out of hand there, I'll head back for Phecon promptly and join up with you all.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: That...
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: I object.
attributes.name: Schwarz

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: I'm aware how wary it is of me to say our sand-burrowing mutants and the safehouse's distress call might not just be coincidence, but the Sargon barrens demand we must maintain vigilance.
attributes.name: Schwarz

attributes.content: We are not clear about the area surrounding Long Spring. Given we are not, you would gamble more alone than you can afford, Rangers, sir.
attributes.name: Schwarz

attributes.content: I'd also like to recommend we move for Long Spring as one. If things aren't friendly for us, we can still cover for each other, especially during a retreat.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: That does make sense.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: Yes, you're right. The old man will listen. I ought to at my age, anyhow. Can't be as spry and reckless as I was in my younger years.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: This thing is ugly as sin.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Ugliness is a personal thing subject to the eye of each beholder. You ought to be seeing through to what this creature embodies, signifies. See through to the myriad array of evolutionary possibilities that it testifies to.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: Order is but our own arbitrarily imposed concept which nature suffers. All the world and its beings were, in their primordiality, chaos seized by impermanence.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: (Russian) Of course, I don't expect any of your sort to understand that in the first place. It's only natural your soft, ignorant little brains can't grasp the grand strokes of the evolutionary scheme.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: A language I know, please!
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Of course, dear sir, setting apart the matter of whether or not it is ugly to you. I must say you are not seeming wholly satisfied with it.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: Else you would not be looking for me in the first place.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: It still isn't strong enough, schoolboy! Your little beastie couldn't even make the lord's escort blink!
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Surely you do not suppose it was down to the sheer incompetence of your ignorant little mercenaries?
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: These mutant creatures are weapons, just weapons. If they knew tactics for themselves, you could throw every mercenary of yours into the garbage heap the next day.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: Bite it, old coot! I'm going to twist your goddamn head off.
attributes.name: Mercenary

attributes.content: Hold it!
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: *Sigh* (facepalm).
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Listen, schoolboy.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: I'm not backing your research so you can talk my ear off about a bunch of high crap. You're here, for me, to solve practical problems.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: I acknowledge it, no mistake. Your research is something else.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: But! If you can't help me depose of my father with it, then you and your little shop of horrors can walk yourselves into the goddamn garbage heap.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: My patience is limited.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: As is mine. I have explained this to you over and over already, and I do not wish to do it again, because I do not wish to waste my time.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: You think you can fool me!
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: I've poured money into your little 'experiments' for half a year, the likes of which you'll never see in your entire goddamn life. And I don't think I've seen an equal return on it!
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Where's that 'cruel and frightening army' you promised me?
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Where's that 'might to make the heart know fear', huh?
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: You think all it takes to keep me happy is a bunch of ugly, swollen, light-up sand beasts?
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: What does it take for you to understand? The fruits of scientific research need time to grow swollen.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: If money was all it took to accelerate the march of science, to ripen the fruit, I would have long since flown away to the moon by now.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: Enough of that. I'll give you two more days. And I want to like what I see.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: (Russian) Imbecile.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: You speak in a language I don't understand one more time, and I'll throw you and all your little creations into the barrenlands to make merry until the sun goes down.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Go on, try me.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: *Sigh*.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: Fetch me some corpses.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: Come again?
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Bring me corpses! People's corpses, corpses like the ones you leave behind! Any will do.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: Of course, ones blighted by the Originium infection will do even better.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: What the hell do you need those for?
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: You bastard old coot. Now you want to insult the dead, huh!
attributes.name: Mercenary

attributes.content: Did you not want the 'might to make the heart know fear'?
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: Then do not hang yourself up on all that pernicious, useless witter you might otherwise call 'ethics'.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: The corpses, bring them to me. I would like to have you see something interesting.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: Chief, this goes completely against the Lord Ameer of Bayalir's great commandments. The old coot is trying to dupe you.
attributes.name: Mercenary

attributes.content: You want to take the dead and raise me some Zhayedans?
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: I do not know whatever this ghoulish thing you call a Zhayedan is, but rest assured you will find confidence in the fruits of my scientific research.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: Chief, I don't think...
attributes.name: Mercenary

attributes.content: Shut up!
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Old boy, I want you to listen carefully.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: You might think you're the peak of intelligence. You might think you've seen every move on the board. You might think there's nothing you don't know.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: But don't think about playing a fast one on me. I've gotten to know your kind all too well.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Everyone like you dies because they think they're too goddamn smart to die.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: The only reason I still put up with you is because you're still useful.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: I can get you what you need.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: But don't disappoint me. Because you will not like what comes after.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Well, then, what else can I possibly say?
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: Good luck to you.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: You're still alive. Don't forget who you have to thank for it.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Without me, your research would amount to a pat of bullshit.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: If not for me, you'd be six months dead, rotting in this ore mine.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: (Sargonian) Head in your ass.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: I'm leaving you two here. Watch him.
attributes.name: Drudge

attributes.content: Got it, boss.
attributes.name: Mercenary

attributes.content: (Russian) Gaggle of imbeciles. Every second I spend talking to you is spent killing off my precious braincells.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.text: The aged scholar reaches the depths of the caverns.
Meandering tunnels lined by frames of cast concrete, set in a particular yet strange pattern.
The things in here were never meant to be here.
Within gray-white metal walls, instruments and devices not of this world wind up into operation.
And within a culture chamber, manufactured of clear glass, Originium enveloped in connective tissue floats.
It contracts. It relaxes. It convulses.

attributes.content: (Russian) Originium...
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: (Russian) It boggles my mind that this world has such an extraordinary existence gracing it.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: (Russian) Yet somehow, these locals fear it in their ignorance. Fear what evolution this great power brings with it.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: (Russian) But no, oh, of course, they should be afraid.
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: (Russian) For the fool fears the unknown. The fool fears might. The fool fears progress...
attributes.name: Levi

attributes.content: (Russian) Ignorants, oh, you ignorants.
attributes.name: Levi
